Jasco, Old Mutual, Royal Bafokeng Platinum: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-08T06:29:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/jasco-old-mutual-royal-bafokeng-platinum-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index declined for a second
day, falling 38.85, or 0.1 percent, to 32,298.21 at the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg.    Anglo American Plc (AGL)  : Copper declined as much as 1
percent on concern that the conflict in Libya and political
unrest in the Middle East may sustain the advance in  oil prices ,
curbing the global economic recovery and hurting demand. Shares
in Anglo dropped 0.1 percent to 373.50 rand.  BHP Billiton Plc (BIL) 
, the world’s largest mining company, fell 0.9 percent
to 277.75 rand.    Ceramic Industries Ltd. (CRM)  : The tile and sink
manufacturer said net income for the six months to Jan. 31 rose
to 88.3 million rand ($12.8 million) from 86.7 million a year
earlier. Shares in the company were unchanged at 137.50 rand.    Compu-Clearing Outsourcing Ltd. (CCL)  : The freight
forwarding and clearing company said net income for the six
months through December rose to 3.7 million rand from 3.2
million rand a year earlier. Shares in the company were
unchanged at 2.40 rand.  Jasco Electronic Holdings Ltd. (JSC SJ): The telecoms
company said earnings per share for the six months through
December will probably be between 65 percent and 75 percent
lower than the 10 cents it reported a year earlier. Jasco was
unchanged at 1.24 rand.    Old Mutual Plc (OML)  : The U.K.’s third-largest insurer
publishes earnings for the year through December. Shares in the
company declined 9 cents, or 0.6 percent, to 15.02 rand.    Royal Bafokeng Platinum Ltd. (RBP)  : The platinum-mining
company posted net income of 3.17 billion rand for the 12 months
to Dec. 31, compared with a loss of 123.4 million rand a year
earlier. The stock climbed 50 cents, or 0.8 percent, to 63.85
rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:    Anglo American Plc (AAL)   slipped 1.4 percent to
$26.38. AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) dropped 0.5 percent to
$47.62. BHP Billiton (BBL US) fell 1.4 percent to $79.76.
DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) gained 1.2 percent to $5.05. Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI US) declined 0.5 percent to $17.49. Harmony Gold
Mining Co. (HMY US) climbed 0.8 percent to $12.20. Impala
Platinum Holdings (IMPUY US) slipped 1.4 percent to $28.95.
Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) fell 1.7 percent to $5.23. Sasol Ltd. (SSL
US) lost 0.5 percent to $55.64.  To contact the reporter on this story:
